claim.claim-text:
1. A method comprising:
receiving a request from a client, at a server comprising a computer system including a hardware processor, to modify content provided within a distributed electronic document retained locally at the client;
identifying, at the server and in response to the request, information associated with the distributed electronic document, the associated information comprising user-dependent association information indicating a second electronic document different from the distributed electronic document;
sending to the client an update to offline access information retained at the client, the update comprising (a) a document revocation list indicating that authorization for the client to modify content provided within the distributed electronic document has been revoked and (b) authorization for the client to modify content provided within the second electronic document; and
relating information concerning the second electronic document from the server to the client, the second electronic document indicated by the user-dependent association information that is dependent on an identified user at the client.

8. The method of claim 1, further comprising:
accessing the distributed electronic document at the client;
identifying an address of the server and a document identifier in the distributed electronic document;
sending the document identifier and the requested modification to the server using the address; and
replacing the distributed electronic document, at the client, with the second electronic document.

13. A method comprising:
opening, at a client comprising a computer including a hardware processor, a locally retained distributed document;
contacting a document control server identified from the distributed document to request authorization to modify content provided within the distributed document;
updating a document revocation list retained at the client based on offline access information received from the document control server, the document revocation list indicating that (a) authorization for the client to modify content provided within the distributed document has been revoked and (b) the client is authorized to modify content provided within a second document; and
forcing modification, at the client, of the second document in place of the distributed document, based on the offline access information received from the document control server;
wherein the second document comprises a later version of the distributed document, and forcing modification comprises transparently closing the distributed document and opening the second document.

18. A software product tangibly embodied in a non-transitory machine-readable medium, the software product comprising instructions configured to cause one or more data processing apparatus to perform operations comprising:
receiving a request from a client, at a server, to modify content provided within a distributed electronic document retained locally at the client;
identifying, at the server and in response to the request, information associated with the distributed electronic document, the associated information comprising user-dependent association information indicating a second electronic document different from and associated with the distributed electronic document;
sending to the client an update to offline access information retained at the client, the update comprising (a) a document revocation list indicating that authorization for the client to modify content provided within the distributed electronic document has been revoked and (b) authorization for the client to modify content provided within the second electronic document; and
relating information concerning the second electronic document from the server to the client, the second electronic document indicated by the user-dependent association information that is dependent on an identified user at the client.

25. The software product of claim 18, wherein the operations further comprise:
accessing the distributed electronic document at the client;
identifying an address of the server and a document identifier in the distributed electronic document;
sending the document identifier and the requested modification to the server using the address; and
replacing the distributed electronic document, at the client, with the second electronic document.

30. A software product tangibly embodied in a non-transitory machine-readable medium, the software product comprising instructions configured to cause one or more data processing apparatus to perform operations comprising:
opening, by a client, a locally retained distributed document;
contacting a document control server identified from the distributed document to request authorization to modify content provided within the distributed document;
updating a document revocation list retained at the client based on offline access information received from the document control server, the document revocation list indicating that (a) authorization for the client to modify content provided within the distributed document has been revoked and (b) the client is authorized to modify content provided within a second document; and
forcing modification of the second document in place of the distributed document based on the offline access information received from the document control server;
wherein the second document comprises a later version of the distributed document, and forcing modification comprises transparently closing the distributed document and opening the second document.
